13/09/2004
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- The head of the National Guard Service (NGS), General Roumen Milanov, said Sunday (12 September) that certain police powers should be granted to his institution in order to enable it to tackle extraordinary situations. Speaking to Bulgarian television, Milanov also said he has ordered concrete measures be taken in response to recent allegations of contacts between NGS members and mafia groups. 
In other news, Croatian Defence Minister Berislav Roncevic kicked off a three-day visit to Bulgaria on Monday. Meetings are expected to focus on ways to enhance bilateral military co-operation, as well as on the stabilisation process in Southeast Europe. (bTV, news.bg - 13/09/04; bTV - 12/09/04) 
